Articles.Content:
This is my first post in the mission reports. The kerbals have only launched 1 probe to duna that was useless. So they wanted to launch more probes to duna and formed. The Duna 23 Explorer Program to launch spacecrafts to duna the first spacecraft will be called the Duna 23 Explorer Orbiter. And it just launched. 

Here is the rocket

![SClIFoG.png](http://i.imgur.com/SClIFoG.png)

Liftoff!

![lJZToOK.png](http://i.imgur.com/lJZToOK.png)

Max Q

![cQxq5Pt.png](http://i.imgur.com/cQxq5Pt.png)

T+ 1:55 First stage separation.

![RPLMtLN.png](http://i.imgur.com/RPLMtLN.png)

First burn of the second stage.

![OStRFYD.png](http://i.imgur.com/OStRFYD.png)

Fairing separation.

![36ldr1y.png](http://i.imgur.com/36ldr1y.png)

First cutoff of the second stage.

![Huj4IZv.png](http://i.imgur.com/Huj4IZv.png)

Second burn of the second stage.

![ppg0uZF.png](http://i.imgur.com/ppg0uZF.png)

Trans-Duna injection.

![3kIOlXg.png](http://i.imgur.com/3kIOlXg.png)

Hope you like it!

**Edited <time datetime="2015-06-26T11:20:08Z" title="06/26/2015 11:20  AM" data-short="9 yr">June 26, 2015</time> by Lime**

Nice photos. I appreciate how they are well lit, not night time. What happened when it arrived at Duna? Did it accomplish the mission? Also, what fuel tanks are those?

For your next mission, I voted for Polar Lander. If you land near the edge of a polar region, you can have a rover visit at least three biomes within a close distance.
I believe those are procedural tanks.

It's crusing to Duna right now.![:)](//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif)
